---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Aninaya Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of Service and EULA for Aninaya — a local-first personal finance app for Android by KaijuBytes."
>
  <section class="py-10">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text);">Aninaya Terms of Service & EULA</h1>
      <p class="text-sm mb-6" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        <strong>Effective date:</strong> May 10, 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong>Last updated:</strong> May 10, 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <a href="/aninaya/privacy-policy/" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Privacy Policy</a>
      </p>

      <div class="rounded-md p-4 mb-8 border-l-4" style="background: var(--color-surface); border-color: var(--color-accent);">
        <strong>Short version:</strong> Aninaya is a personal-use Android app published by
        KaijuBytes (sole trader, Philippines). It assists you in tracking finances and
        preparing your SALN — but it is <em>not</em> a regulated financial adviser, and
        it is <em>not</em> an official Civil Service Commission product. AI features
        produce drafts only; you are responsible for reviewing them. Subscriptions are
        billed through Google Play and can be cancelled there at any time.
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">1. Acceptance</h2>
      <p>
        By installing or using Aninaya you agree to these Terms of Service and the
        accompanying <a href="/aninaya/privacy-policy/" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Privacy Policy</a>.
        If you do not agree, do not install or use the app. Inside the app, your
        acceptance is recorded with a timestamp and a checksum of the version you saw
        — when these terms are updated you will be hard-blocked from continued use
        until you re-accept.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">2. End-User Licence Agreement (EULA)</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">
        Aninaya is licensed to you (end user) for personal, non-commercial use on
        Android devices you own or control. You may not:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-3">
        <li>Reverse-engineer, decompile, or disassemble the app except as expressly
            permitted by Philippine law (e.g. interoperability under fair use).</li>
        <li>Resell, sublicense, or commercially redistribute the app, the on-device
            AI model files, or any extracted asset.</li>
        <li>Use the app to process or store the personal data of third parties
            without their explicit consent.</li>
        <li>Bypass the in-app purchase system to unlock Pro / Elite features.</li>
        <li>Use the app for any purpose contrary to applicable Philippine law,
            including the Anti-Money Laundering Act (RA 9160) and the Data Privacy
            Act (RA 10173).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Copyright in the app, including all source code shipped to your device,
        belongs to <strong>Orlando G. Martinez (Lanz) / KaijuBytes</strong>. The on-device
        AI models bundled with or downloaded by the app (Qwen 2.5, Qwen3, SmolLM,
        MiniLM) remain governed by their respective Apache 2.0 / source licences.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">3. Subscription Terms</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">
        Aninaya offers a Free tier and paid tiers (Pro and Elite/Family). Paid tiers
        are billed through <strong>Google Play Billing</strong>. Current prices are
        shown on the upgrade screen inside the app and on your Google Play subscription
        page — they are managed by Google Play and may change. This document does
        not commit to any specific peso amount.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-3">
        <li>Subscriptions auto-renew unless cancelled at least 24 hours before the
            renewal date, in line with Google Play policy.</li>
        <li>You can cancel at any time in your Google Play account.</li>
        <li>Refund requests are handled by Google Play in the first instance; please
            contact <a href="https://support.google.com/googleplay" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Google Play Support</a> for refunds.</li>
        <li>If a paid feature stops working or fails to deliver a service that was
            advertised at the time of purchase, contact
            <a href="mailto:support@kaijubytes.dev" style="color: var(--color-accent);">support@kaijubytes.dev</a>
            and we will work with you to resolve it.</li>
        <li>Pro and Elite features are convenience automation tools — they do not
            constitute the sale of government forms or certified financial advice.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">4. SALN Module</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">
        Aninaya assists in preparing the <strong>Statement of Assets, Liabilities and
        Net Worth (SALN)</strong> form for Philippine government employees. Important
        clarifications:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-3">
        <li>Aninaya is <strong>not</strong> affiliated with the Civil Service
            Commission (CSC), the Office of the Ombudsman, or any other Philippine
            government agency.</li>
        <li>Aninaya is <strong>not</strong> an official CSC product. The DOCX/PDF
            outputs use the CSC Resolution No. 2500632 templates, but generation
            and content remain your responsibility.</li>
        <li>You are <strong>solely responsible</strong> for the accuracy,
            completeness, and lawful submission of your SALN. KaijuBytes is not
            liable for omissions, errors, or misclassifications in the generated
            forms.</li>
        <li>The SALN module asks for your explicit confirmation each time you export
            a form. The exported file is written to your device — KaijuBytes never
            receives a copy.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">5. No Financial Advice</h2>
      <p>
        Aninaya is a personal budgeting and tracking tool. The AI Planner, AI Chat,
        coaching tips, debt-payoff projections, and net-worth reports are
        <strong>informational only</strong>. Nothing in the app constitutes regulated
        financial advice, investment recommendation, tax advice, or insurance
        guidance. Consult a licensed financial planner, CPA, or insurance adviser
        before acting on figures the app produces.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">6. AI-Generated Content</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">
        Aninaya's AI features (Receipt AI, Statement Scan, AI Chat, AI Planner)
        produce <strong>drafts only</strong>. By using these features you agree that:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-3">
        <li>OCR and AI extraction accuracy depends on receipt quality, device tier,
            and the on-device model in use. You will review every extracted field
            before saving.</li>
        <li>AI Chat / Planner replies are pattern-matched suggestions, not certified
            advice. You will verify any actionable guidance against official sources
            (BSP, BIR, SSS, GSIS, Pag-IBIG, your bank, your insurer, your employer)
            before acting on it.</li>
        <li>You will not rely on AI output alone for tax filings, regulatory
            disclosures (including SALN), legal proceedings, or investment decisions.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        On first use of any AI feature, the app records your acknowledgement of these
        limitations. You can revisit the explanation at any time in
        <em>Settings → AI &amp; Planning → How on-device AI works</em>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">7. Bring-Your-Own AI Provider Risk</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">
        Aninaya supports connecting your own AI endpoint (OpenAI, Anthropic, hosted
        Ollama, LM Studio, or any OpenAI-compatible API) for AI Chat. If you enable
        this:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-3">
        <li>A financial context summary (account names, balances, debt utilization,
            salary average, employer if set, active goals, recurring bills, trips)
            is sent to that provider for each chat turn. See the
            <a href="/aninaya/privacy-policy/#5b" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Privacy Policy § 5b</a>
            for the full list.</li>
        <li>Your data leaves your device the moment you press Send. KaijuBytes never
            sees this traffic but cannot make any representations about how the
            receiving provider stores, retains, or uses it.</li>
        <li>You are responsible for understanding the third-party provider's privacy
            posture, terms of service, and data residency. KaijuBytes is not liable
            for losses arising from the third-party provider's handling of your data.</li>
        <li>The app prompts a per-host consent dialog before sending data to a new
            base URL, and refuses to send to non-loopback hosts you have not
            approved.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">8. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">
        The app is provided "<strong>as is</strong>" and "<strong>as available</strong>"
        without warranties of any kind, whether express, implied, or statutory,
        including but not limited to warranties of merchantability, fitness for a
        particular purpose, and non-infringement. KaijuBytes does not warrant that:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-3">
        <li>The app will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of malicious code.</li>
        <li>OCR or AI extraction will be accurate in any specific case.</li>
        <li>The app will be compatible with all Android devices, OS versions, or
            third-party apps.</li>
        <li>Data stored on your device will survive device failure, OS reinstall,
            uninstallation, or unauthorised access. <strong>You are responsible</strong>
            for backing up your encrypted vault export to a location you trust.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by Philippine law, in no event shall
        KaijuBytes be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential,
        or punitive damages — including loss of profits, data, financial records,
        or government penalties — arising from your use of or inability to use the
        app. KaijuBytes' total cumulative liability for any claim relating to the
        app shall not exceed the greater of: (a) PHP 500, or (b) the amount you
        paid KaijuBytes for the app in the 12 months preceding the claim.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">10. Termination</h2>
      <p>
        You may stop using Aninaya at any time by uninstalling it. KaijuBytes may
        suspend or terminate your access to paid features if you breach these Terms,
        though no termination action will require you to delete data already stored
        on your own device. Sections 5 (No Financial Advice), 8 (Disclaimer), 9
        (Limitation of Liability), and 12 (Governing Law) survive termination.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">11. Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms when adding new features, addressing regulatory
        changes, or clarifying existing provisions. The updated Terms will be posted
        at this URL with a new effective date. The in-app version of the Terms is
        accompanied by a checksum of the body text — when either the date or the
        checksum changes, the app will hard-block existing users into a re-acceptance
        flow on next launch. You may decline the updated Terms; doing so will close
        the app.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">12. Governing Law &amp; Jurisdiction</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of the Republic of the Philippines.
        Any dispute arising out of or in connection with these Terms shall be
        subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Metro Manila,
        Philippines. Nothing in this clause limits any consumer-protection right
        you have under Philippine law that cannot be waived by contract.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">13. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms:<br />
        <a href="mailto:support@kaijubytes.dev" style="color: var(--color-accent);">support@kaijubytes.dev</a><br />
        KaijuBytes (sole trader, Orlando G. Martinez / Lanz)<br />
        Philippines
      </p>

      <footer class="mt-12 pt-6 text-sm" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); color: var(--color-muted);">
        © 2026 Orlando G. Martinez (Lanz) / KaijuBytes. All rights reserved.
        Aninaya is not a regulated financial adviser. Information in the app
        is for personal budgeting and planning purposes only.
      </footer>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
